'''Azarias Emmanuel Londoño González''' (born 21 June 2001) is a Panamanian professional footballer who plays as [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[C.D. Universidad Católica del Ecuador|Universidad Católica]], on loan from [[Alianza F.C. (Panama)|Alianza]], and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].

==Club career==
===Alianza===
Londoño began his senior career with [[Alianza F.C. (Panama)|Alianza]] in 2020.

====2021: Loan to O&M====
In 2021, he joined the Dominican club  [[O&M FC|O&M]] on loan for the season.

====2022: Return to Alianza and first league title====
Returning to Alianza, He helped them win the [[2022 Liga Panameña de Fútbol]].<ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://www.panamaamerica.com.pa/deportes/alianza-campeon-apertura-2022-de-la-lpf-1207453|title=Alianza, campeón Apertura 2022 de la LPF|date=28 May 2022|website=Panamá América}}</ref>

====2022–23: Loan to Comunicaciones====
On 18 August 2022, he was loaned out to the [[Liga Nacional de Fútbol de Guatemala]] side [[Comunicaciones F.C.|Comunicaciones]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.publinews.gt/gt/deportes/2022/08/18/panameno-azarias-londono-es-nuevo-fichaje-de-comunicaciones.html|title=Panameño Azarías Londoño es nuevo fichaje de Comunicaciones|date=18 August 2022|website=Publinews}}</ref>

====2023–24: Loan spells at Torreense and Comunicaciones====
On 12 July 2023, he was then loaned to the [[Liga Portugal 2]] side [[S.C.U. Torreense|Torreense]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rpctv.com/futbol-internacional/futbol/azarias-londono-dice-adios-guatemala-ahora-jugara-europa-n5900659|title=Azarías Londoño dice adiós a Guatemala, ahora jugará en Europa|website=www.rpctv.com}}</ref>

On 27 January 2024, he returned again to Comunicaciones on loan for the 2024 season.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.prensalibre.com/deportes/futbol-nacional/comunicaciones-oficializa-la-vuelta-de-azarias-londono-tras-su-breve-periodo-en-portugal/|title=Comunicaciones oficializa la vuelta de Azarías Londoño tras su breve período en Portugal|date=7 January 2024}}</ref>

====2025–26: Loan to Universidad Católica====
On 8 January 2025, he joined the [[Ecuadorian Serie A]] club [[C.D. Universidad Católica del Ecuador|Universidad Católica]] on loan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.primicias.ec/deportes/azarias-londono-universidad-catolica-ecuador-86999/|title=El panameño Azarias Londoño es nuevo delantero de Universidad Católica|date=8 January 2025|website=Primicias}}</ref>

==International career==
===Youth===
Londoño was called up to the [[Panama national under-20 football team|Panama U20]] for the [[2022 Maurice Revello Tournament]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Los convocados para el Torneo Maurice Revello |url=https://fepafut.com/los-convocados-para-el-torneo-maurice-revello/ |publisher=Federación Panameña de Fútbol |date=23 May 2022 |language=es}}</ref>

===Senior===
Londoño debuted with the made the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]] in a friendly 2–0 win over [[Bahrain national football team|Bahrain]] on 27 September 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rpctv.com/marea-roja/azarias-londono-es-el-fruto-hacer-las-cosas-bien-n5860392|title=Azarías Londoño: “Es el fruto de hacer las cosas bien”|website=www.rpctv.com}}</ref> He was part of the squad for the [[2023 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://fepafut.com/los-23-elegidos-para-la-copa-oro/|title=Los 23 elegidos para la Copa Oro|trans-title=The 23 selected for the Gold Cup|publisher=[[Panamanian Football Federation]]|date=19 June 2023|access-date=19 June 2023|language=es}}</ref> He again made the final Panama squad for the [[2025 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Da Silva |first1=Alexander |title=COMUNICADO OFICIAL |url=https://www.fepafut.com/blog/2025/06/11/comunicado-oficial-16/ |website=www.fepafut.com |publisher=[[Panamanian Football Federation]] |access-date=13 June 2025 |language=es |date=11 June 2025 |quote=José Fajardo y Cecilio Waterman serán baja de la convocatoria para Copa Oro de CONCACAF por lesión... convocó a los jugadores Gustavo Herrera y Kahiser Lenis, de la lista preliminar de 60 seleccionados.}}</ref>

